### What to Do

Create reusable functions that apply consistent Panel styling based on severity level. This ensures all denial/warning boxes have appropriate visual weight.

### Severity Visual Hierarchy

| Severity | Border | Color | Icon | Box Style |
|----------|--------|-------|------|-----------|
| Critical | Double | bright_red | 🛑 | BoxStyle::double() |
| High | Heavy | red | ⚠️ | BoxStyle::heavy() |
| Medium | Rounded | yellow | ⚡ | BoxStyle::rounded() |
| Low | Simple | blue | ℹ️ | BoxStyle::simple() |

### Implementation

```rust
pub fn create_severity_panel(
    content: &str,
    severity: Severity,
    title: Option<&str>,
) -> Panel {
    let (icon, color, box_style) = match severity {
        Severity::Critical => ("🛑", "bright_red", BoxStyle::double()),
        Severity::High => ("⚠️", "red", BoxStyle::heavy()),
        Severity::Medium => ("⚡", "yellow", BoxStyle::rounded()),
        Severity::Low => ("ℹ️", "blue", BoxStyle::simple()),
    };

    let title_text = title
        .map(|t| format!("[bold {}]{} {}[/]", color, icon, t))
        .unwrap_or_else(|| format!("[bold {}]{}[/]", color, icon));

    Panel::from_text(content)
        .title(&title_text)
        .box_style(box_style)
        .border_style(Style::new().color(color))
        .padding((1, 2))
}
```

### ASCII Fallback

For terminals that don't support Unicode:
```rust
let (icon, box_style) = match severity {
    Severity::Critical => ("[!]", BoxStyle::ascii_double()),
    Severity::High => ("[!]", BoxStyle::ascii()),
    Severity::Medium => ("[*]", BoxStyle::ascii()),
    Severity::Low => ("[i]", BoxStyle::ascii()),
};
```

### Usage

```rust
// In DenialBox
let panel = create_severity_panel(
    &content,
    self.severity.unwrap_or(Severity::High),
    Some("COMMAND BLOCKED"),
);
```
